              <div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I'm obviously not the only one here that's noticed it, so recognizing the fact that you are generally negative isn't much of an 'ignorant generalization'.<br /></div><br /><br />Actually, this proxy thing is a huge personality shift. Back during the earliest threads, I was the one arguing magic was way too expensive and he was telling me that ingenuity beats net deckers on any day of the week and $5 decks were tearing up his legacy circuit, where a buddy of his stumbled upon fluctuator.dec without ever hearing anyone else talk about it.<br /><br />*fluctuator.dec example for the two people who haven't seen it before:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://forums.mtgsalvation.com/showthread.php?t=45360">http://forums.mtgsalvation.com/showthread.php?t=45360</a><!-- m -->

              

              
              
